race.comment: Hayes-trained MISS ALTAIR (6) brought strong form in better grade to resumption and looked a run short. Is proven second-up and likes to position forward. Will be tough to beat. DEMOJO (2) seeks the hat-trick off an easy third-up win at Ballarat. Keeps getting better and is on a quick backup. Promising and tough to beat. DOCUMENTARY (5) was plainer at Pakenham, but the form prior stacks up. A player with average luck in the run. ICY POLE (11) has been racing well without winning. Finally draws and inside gate and Yendall replaces the apprentice. Goes in on an each-way basis. BINE (8) fitter for recent racing and worth including.
